    .desc = A barrel loaded with gunpowder and nails. Anti-personnel shrapnel from the world of medieval artillery. Average spread, average speed of arrival.
    .suffix = { "Medieval, catapult ammunition" }
ent-MedievalCatapultAmmoBarrelAp = catapult core
    .desc = Extremely powerful and accurate, but small projectile for a catapult. No spread, fast arrival speed. Extremely effective against walls.
    .suffix = { "Medieval, catapult ammunition" }
ent-MedievalCatapultAmmoBarrelStone = rounded boulder
    .desc = A boulder that can be loaded into a catapult. The accuracy leaves much to be desired. The spread is large, the speed of arrival is slow. It will help when you need to demolish gates or walls.
    .suffix = { "Medieval, catapult ammunition" }
ent-MedievalCatapultCraft = catapult work piece
    .desc = Attention! There are currently problems with the catapult moving between map sectors, so it is best to place this blank before the siege, in the desired sector. Click with the blank in your active hand on the place where you want to place the object to craft the catapult.
    .suffix = { "Medieval" }
